<p class="page" id="a3802034">[Page 34]</p>
<p>15-12-16<br/>along the line &amp; met the linesman from Bde H.Q. repairing a break about a mile from Bde. sig Office, it was then dark &amp; I had 3 miles to come back over strange country but I took good care not to get too far East &amp; eventually found half a mile West of the Camp &amp; was here halted by a Tommy Outpost, was having tea when the line broke again so Olson &amp; I mounted up &amp; went out again &amp; found the telephone line about 2 miles from Camp tapped in &amp; found the Bde linesman had mended it so we returned arriving back in camp at 10 oclock tonight. The troops had to take<br/>their horses to railhead (2 miles) to water this afternoon as the wells are hardly ready.</p>
